    "# Function 2: Calculate Raster Statistics 📊\n",
    "\n",
    "**Welcome to raster data analysis!**\n",
    "\n",
    "In this notebook, you'll learn how to build the `calculate_raster_statistics()` function step by step. This is like running raster statistics in QGIS - but with full control over the process and the ability to handle NoData values properly.\n",
    "\n",
    "## 🎯 What This Function Does\n",
    "- Reads a specific band from a raster file\n",
    "- Handles NoData values by masking them out of calculations\n",
    "- Calculates essential statistics: min, max, mean, standard deviation\n",
    "- Computes percentiles (25th, 50th, 75th) for data distribution analysis\n",
    "- Counts valid pixels vs. NoData pixels\n",
    "- Returns organized statistics for further analysis\n",
    "- Handles different data types and ranges appropriately\n",
    "\n",
    "## 🔧 Function Signature\n",
    "```python\n",
    "def calculate_raster_statistics(raster_path, band_number=1):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Args:\n",
    "        raster_path (str): Path to raster file (e.g., 'data/elevation_dem.tif')\n",
    "        band_number (int): Which band to analyze (1-based indexing, default=1)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "        dict: Dictionary containing comprehensive statistics for the band\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "```"
   ]
